The classic recursive solution to a factorial algorithm:

```rust
fn factorial(n: i32) -> i32 {
    if n == 0 {
        1
    } else {
        n * factorial(n - 1)
    }
}
```

This example illustrates how the core problem is defined within the base case, creating an inherently simpler tree of function calls. The function calls itself with a reduced problem size, producing a direct, closed-form result.
